[The updated OIE outbreak summary as of 9 Oct 2019, presenting the summed-up accumulated data of this sheep pox event, which officially started 10 Jul 2019, are as follows:
Total outbreaks = 11 (submitted)
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 1176 / 123 / 14 / 76 / 0

The causative virus strain involved in the current and previous outbreaks in Russia seems to affect sheep exclusively (no cases reported from goats).

Vaccination data are not presented. The sheep & goat pox virus vaccine applied in Russia is, to the best of our knowledge, a live attenuated sheep pox vaccine ("ARRIAH" strain). - Mod.AS

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Tver oblast, Russia: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6720644,432]
